data.title: Gainesville Daily Register
data.meta_description: Carol Williams passed away. This is the full obituary where you can share condolences and memories. Published in the Gainesville Daily Register on 2023-02-20.
data.text:
Carol (Mabry) Williams. AKA Carol Orsburn (84) passed away peacefully at Medical Center Plano Texas on February 12th, 2023, surrounded by her family. Carol was born in Gainesville, Texas on August 21st, 1938. She was the 3rd child of John Bunyan and Gertrude Mabry. She was preceded in death by her parents and three brothers J.B. Mabry Jr., Olion Wayne Mabry, and Delmar Clint Mabry, one grandchild Krisha Mangrum, and one great- grandchild Anna Michelle Kaiser.

She is survived by her sister and brother-in-law, Dorothy and Wayne Cooper of Joshua Texas, Three sons Michael Orsburn and wife Susan of Valley View Texas, Larkin and Helena Orsburn of Muenster Texas, and Kent and Linda Orsburn of Myra Texas. 11 grandchildren, and 7 great-grandchildren and 5 great-great grandchildren.

Carol was a member of Era Baptist Church of Era TX. Carol worked for FEMA for 26 years as a case worker and trainer. She retired from FEMA in 2013. Carol loved playing electronic games.

Memorial Services to be held 2:00 p.m., Friday February 24th, 2023 at Denton Bible Church Little Chapel (this is the small chapel in front of the main auditorium) Located at 2300 East University, Denton TX, 76209

Published on February 20, 2023
